── OPEN ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Improve platform based updater
    - Difficult inside Docker: container build is the blocker. Most users are on
      espeak which runs everywhere. Possible approach: map entire /app volume
      (including node_modules) and do a hot-swap, but multi-stage builds
      complicate this significantly.

Multi-arch Docker image
    - x86_64 only currently. ARM (Raspberry Pi, Apple Silicon hosts) not tested.

Expose voiceRate in /settings UI
    - Currently settable via BotSettings.set('voiceRate', N) but not surfaced to
      users. Only affects macOS `say` provider.

Add ONNX voice model change option via /settings
    - piperModel path is in settings.json; needs a curl/wget download flow since
      Discord upload limit makes direct attachment impractical.
    - Consider per-model library subfolder so switching models doesn't nuke
      cached samples from another model.

Pre-generate number library when model changes
    - Currently deferred until first /launch. If a user switches mid-session they
      may wait unexpectedly. Could call initializeNumberLibrary() immediately
      after a provider/model change.

Periodic cleanup of stale intro files (> 1 month old)

Piper as HTTP service
    - Running as a persistent HTTP daemon avoids 350 MB RAM reload per synthesis
      call (piper loads model fresh each execFile call). Trade-off: memory always
      committed vs. loaded on demand.

Centralized generation server / shared voice model hosting

Train custom voice models

Multi-arch Docker support

